-- Lexer error: a `\u{…}` escape with NO digits. The other face of #592, same root —
-- the digit run was never required to be non-empty, so an empty run parsed as
-- `charFromCode 0` and `"a\u{}b"` silently produced a NUL byte (61 00 62) at exit 0.
-- U+0000 is a perfectly valid scalar value, so no range check could ever see this;
-- only requiring a non-empty run can. (A NUL a user ASKED for — `\u{0}` — still lexes:
-- the defect was fabricating one from an empty escape, not the codepoint itself.)
-- A half-finished edit is exactly how you get `\u{}`.
x = "a\u{}b"
